formatted_address: 18 Sin Ming Ln, Midview City, Singapore 573960
name: The Canteen

reviews.text:
23/7/2024
Had Claypot Rice ($8) from Ah Ching Claypot Delights, was extremely good.
Had Sundubu Jjigae ($7) from Wooga Jjajang & Bimbowl, was normal.
Lots of other stalls to try, I'll be back!
Ah Ching Claypot Delights stall - tastes excellent, prices are reasonable. After ordering, wait 20 mins to collect (pager beeping).

Ate chicken rice and few foods few times. Surprisingly delicious. All were wearing face mask and polite. Price was reasonable. The only food I haven tasted is the indian food. The indian man serving the food did not wear mask. Food was open. Only one wore mask.

Avocado milkshake from juice farm is 2.50 here, 50c cheaper than juice farm outlets in shopping malls, but tastes a little weird sometimes, like not fresh. Wanton noodles with charsiew add roasted pork at 5 bucks was very tasty, aunties serving me was polite and friendly. Taste of Thailand pineapple fried rice was 5 bucks, my daughter loves it and keeps asking for it. Indulge grilled chicken rice with edamame, onsen egg and corn was 6.90, tasty too! Will be back to try the duck rice and kway chap.
guess this is mostly catered for working people around the area. not much stalls opened on a Sunday afternoon. but the Thai food is commendable.
